Design and implement an abstraction layer in ralph.py to support multiple AI runtimes. Create a base `AIRunner` abstract class with common interface methods: `run_task(task_id, branch_name)` that returns completion status and output. Define the contract that all runtime implementations must follow including: command execution, output capture, error handling, and timeout management. This enables plugging in different AI tools (Aider, Cursor, Cline, Codex) without changing the core ralph loop logic. The abstraction should handle runtime detection, version checking, and graceful degradation when a runtime is unavailable.

